    "content": "nullSales Performance Management\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Sales Performance Management\n Sales Planning\n Sales Planning Setup\n Data Sources Management\n Create a Sales Plan\n Segmentation\n Considerations for Segmentation\n Segment Business Units and Record Assignments\n Territory Planning\n Quota Planning\n Quota Attainment Planning\n Legacy Sales Planning\n Incentive Compensation Management\n Release Notes for Sales Performance Management\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALES PERFORMANCE MANAGEMENT\nSegment Business Units and Record Assignments\n\nAlign business units with your business objectives when you segment records and assignments by location, industry, and any demographics from your data sources in Sales Planning.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\nAvailable in: both Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience\nAvailable for an additional cost in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with Sales Planning in English only, and only if you have Web Services API enabled\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo establish hierarchies:\t\n\nData Pipelines Base User permission set license\n\nData Pipelines Base User permission set\n\nAND\n\nSales Planning permission set\n\nIn Sales Planning, select your sales plan, and then click Create Segments.\nSegment from the top part of your sales hierarchy, and then assign users and records to those segments. Split the top segments by a field. Click Add New Segment, and then give it a name.\nFor example, you segment by country, so you split your segment by Billing Country.\nCreate other segments from splits, or further split segments into smaller ones when you select specific fields depending on your goal. For example, you create a segment for the AMER region that includes accounts in the Americas.\nFurther split segments depending on your business objectives. For example, segment by industry.\nFor example, you further segment AMER by industry.\nDelegate planning authority to team leaders and members from any segment.\nSave your changes.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
